rying the free parameters\n$a$ and $b$ for a fixed loop of $\\rho_0 = 10^{-11}$\\, kg $\\text{m}^{-3}$, $T_0\n= 6.3$\\, MK and loop length $L= 180$\\, Mm. We find that the consideration of\ndifferent heating functions [$H(\\rho,T)$] leads to a significant variation in\nthe phase difference between density and temperature perturbations; however,\nthe polytropic index remains close to a value of 1.66.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 9 Dec 2021 15:40:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-01-19"}
